66 /*
67 * Mail source classes. Used to specify policy decisions for content
68 * inspection and SMTPUTF8 detection.
69 */
70#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_SENDMAIL "sendmail" /* sendmail(1) */
71#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_SMTPD "smtpd" /* smtpd(8) */
72#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_QMQPD "qmqpd" /* qmqpd(8) */
73#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_FORWARD "forward" /* local(8) forward/alias */
74#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_BOUNCE "bounce"/* bounce(8) */
75#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_NOTIFY "notify"/* protocol etc. errors */
76#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_VERIFY "verify"/* protocol etc. errors */
77#define MAIL_SRC_NAME_ALL "all" /* all sources */
78
79#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_SENDMAIL (1<<0) /* sendmail(1) */
80#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_SMTPD (1<<1) /* smtpd(8) */
81#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_QMQPD (1<<2) /* qmqpd(8) */
82#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_FORWARD (1<<3) /* local(8) forward/alias */
83#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_BOUNCE (1<<4) /* bounce(8) */
84#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_NOTIFY (1<<5) /* protocol etc. errors */
85#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_VERIFY (1<<6) /* protocol etc. errors */
86
87#define MAIL_SRC_MASK_ALL \
88 ( MAIL_SRC_MASK_SENDMAIL | MAIL_SRC_MASK_SMTPD \
89 | MAIL_SRC_MASK_QMQPD | MAIL_SRC_MASK_FORWARD \
90 | MAIL_SRC_MASK_BOUNCE | MAIL_SRC_MASK_NOTIFY \
91 | MAIL_SRC_MASK_VERIFY)
92
93 /*
94 * Well-known socket or FIFO directories. The main difference is in file
95 * access permissions.
96 */
97#define MAIL_CLASS_PUBLIC "public"
98#define MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE "private"
99
100 /*
101 * Generic triggers.
102 */
103#define TRIGGER_REQ_WAKEUP 'W' /* wakeup */
104
105 /*
106 * Queue manager requests.
107 */
108#define QMGR_REQ_SCAN_DEFERRED 'D' /* scan deferred queue */
109#define QMGR_REQ_SCAN_INCOMING 'I' /* scan incoming queue */
110#define QMGR_REQ_FLUSH_DEAD 'F' /* flush dead xport/site */
111#define QMGR_REQ_SCAN_ALL 'A' /* ignore time stamps */

121extern char *mail_pathname(const char *, const char *);

200 /*
201 * The following attribute names are stored in queue files. Changing this
202 * means lots of work to maintain backwards compatibility with queued mail.
203 */
204#define MAIL_ATTR_ENCODING "encoding" /* internal encoding */
205#define MAIL_ATTR_ENC_8BIT "8bit" /* 8BITMIME equivalent */
206#define MAIL_ATTR_ENC_7BIT "7bit" /* 7BIT equivalent */
207#define MAIL_ATTR_ENC_NONE "" /* encoding unknown */

213#define MAIL_ATTR_LOG_PROTO_NAME "log_protocol_name" /* SMTP/ESMTP/QMQP */

243#define XCLIENT_PORT "PORT" /* client port */
244#define XCLIENT_PROTO "PROTO" /* client protocol */
245#define XCLIENT_HELO "HELO" /* client helo */
246#define XCLIENT_LOGIN "LOGIN" /* SASL login name */
247
248#define XCLIENT_UNAVAILABLE "[UNAVAILABLE]" /* permanently unavailable */
249#define XCLIENT_TEMPORARY "[TEMPUNAVAIL]" /* temporarily unavailable */
